title: Where are They Now? Jonathan King - PrepXtra
text:
Dead End BBQ's Where are they Now?
Jonathan King
Tennessee Tech, punter
Farragut High School
Now: King, a 6-foot-3, 180-pound sophomore, is averaging 41.2 yards per punt this season. Elevend of his 45 kicks have been downed inside the 20-yard line. He had a season-long punt of 58 yards at Houston. In 2014, he had a career-long punt of 63 yards and led the Ohio Valley Conference with a 41.5-yard average, which ranked 21st in the FCS.
Then: King was named Mr. Football Kicker of the Year, and Ray Guy's ProKicker.com National Player of the Year as a senior in 2012, averaging 46.9 yards per punt for the Admirals. He made 35 of 37 PATs and six of nine field-goal attempts.
Chris Thomas
